HEADWORD: Shirred
<hw>Shirred</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Sewing)</fld> <def>Made or gathered into a shirr; <as>as, a
<ex>shirred</ex> bonnet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>Broken into an earthen dish and
baked over the fire; -- said of eggs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shirt</ent>⟦br⟧
